In rare cases where a secondary tablet is attached to allow easier handling on the lap as opposed to working on the screen tablet on the table, similar pager to the stylii is used for the tablet devices.
Extremely rare case of having concurrent tablets
There are cases when multiple stylii can be conected. This is mostly useful for mapping software tools to physical devices.

I came to the conclusion a different tip feel for the same kind of stylus is not something that should be achieved by individually tweaking the slider per device, but can be achieved by the tool/brush setting itself (simulating different hardness of a pencil for example).
There are however differnt classes of stylii that should allow to map function to particular features.

Default stylus type (1button/2button) can be linked to a tablet model. When an additional stylus device gets close/registered, UI updates to show the active stylus class and a pager is shown next to the device name. The stylii list is not cached.
Special case of multiple stylii
